This paper deals with the problem of causal discovery, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a new method for causal discovery based on a Kernel Intrinsic Invariance Measure (KIIM). This involves using kernel methods to capture higher order statistics of conditional distributions, which is a technique commonly used in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
